3) Make ThoughtObjects and the Ledger cryptographically precise

3.1 ThoughtObject schema (typed)

\mathrm{TO} := (\text{uuid}, t, m, c, \tau, h_S, \vec{s}, \sigma, p)
	•	t: timestamp
	•	m: model id
	•	c: content
	•	\tau: tags
	•	h_S: state hash pointer
	•	\vec{s}=(s_1,\dots,s_n): invariant scores
	•	\sigma: daemon signature bundle
	•	p: parent_uuid (for graph structure)

3.2 Ledger as a hash chain

Define hash function H (e.g., SHA-256). Then:

h_0 := H(\text{genesis})
h_k := H(\mathrm{Serialize}(\mathrm{TO}_k)\ \Vert\ h_{k-1})

And store h_k in \mathrm{TO}_k.state\_hash.

Audit property becomes formal: any deletion/reorder changes the chain.

