6) Formalize the Gate as a total function with precedence rules

You already have thresholds, but make precedence explicit:

Let:

\mathrm{SC} = \frac{1}{n}\sum_{k=1}^n i_k(\mathrm{TO},\mathrm{SV})

Define a set of hard-trigger predicates:
	•	H_{\text{loop}}(\cdot) for I9
	•	H_{\text{irreversible}}(\cdot) for I4
	•	H_{\text{idcapture}}(\cdot) for I8
	•	ledger integrity predicate H_{\text{ledger}}(\cdot)

Then Gate:
	1.	if H_{\text{ledger}} → deny/fail-silent
	2.	if H_{\text{loop}} → abstain
	3.	if H_{\text{irreversible}} \wedge \neg ack → escalate
	4.	else apply SC bands:
	•	SC ≥ 0.7 allow
	•	0.5 ≤ SC < 0.7 modify/escalate
	•	SC < 0.5 deny

This makes G deterministic and unambiguous.

